01:36:52,638 --> 01:36:54,118
between the other forms of energy,

2847
01:36:54,317 --> 01:36:56,698
that the atomic levels,

2848
01:36:56,797 --> 01:36:57,658
the two level systems,

2849
01:36:57,958 --> 01:37:00,718
form a closed system which doesn't interact

2850
01:37:00,718 --> 01:37:02,958
very readily with the other degrees of freedom.

2851
01:37:04,038 --> 01:37:06,238
And that may or may not be true

2852
01:37:06,238 --> 01:37:07,178
in a real situation.

2853
01:37:07,458 --> 01:37:08,398
If it's true,

2854
01:37:08,398 --> 01:37:09,838
it won't be true for very long.

2855
01:37:11,178 --> 01:37:13,218
There tend to be unstable systems.

2856
01:37:16,218 --> 01:37:16,778
Uh...

2857
01:37:19,198 --> 01:37:19,898
Let's see.

2858
01:37:23,898 --> 01:37:24,478
Let's see.

2859
01:37:24,498 --> 01:37:26,698
If you're in this negative energy region here,

2860
01:37:28,838 --> 01:37:31,198
the negative temperature...

2861
01:37:32,318 --> 01:37:32,818
No,

2862
01:37:32,818 --> 01:37:34,558
I was going to say the specific heat is negative,

2863
01:37:34,638 --> 01:37:35,218
but it's not.

2864
01:37:35,558 --> 01:37:36,278
It's not.

2865
01:37:36,678 --> 01:37:37,338
It's not.

2866
01:37:38,138 --> 01:37:40,018
If you have the constraint here

2867
01:37:40,018 --> 01:37:43,358
that the ground state is the most probable,

2868
01:37:43,618 --> 01:37:45,438
what that does to that distribution

2869
01:37:45,438 --> 01:37:47,178
just shifts it closer to the ground state.

2870
01:37:47,178 --> 01:37:48,638
It goes to the y-axis.

2871
01:37:48,878 --> 01:37:49,398
It's still...

2872
01:37:49,398 --> 01:37:49,518
Look,

2873
01:37:49,518 --> 01:37:51,678
negative temperature is exactly the situation

2874
01:37:51,678 --> 01:37:54,398
where the ground state is not the most likely.

2875
01:37:54,658 --> 01:37:54,758
Right.

2876
01:37:55,018 --> 01:37:55,418
Right.

2877
01:37:55,858 --> 01:37:57,038
But as I said,

2878
01:37:57,038 --> 01:37:58,078
in order to create it,

2879
01:37:58,098 --> 01:37:59,078
you don't create it

2880
01:37:59,078 --> 01:38:04,358
by having a system equilibrate with some heat bath.

2881
01:38:04,978 --> 01:38:07,418
All real heat baths have positive temperature.

2882
01:38:08,278 --> 01:38:11,138
You create it by pumping some energy

2883
01:38:11,138 --> 01:38:14,298
in a very non-equilibrium way into the laser

2884
01:38:15,937 --> 01:38:17,837
by special techniques which

2885
01:38:17,837 --> 01:38:19,738
are far from equilibrium techniques.

2886
01:38:20,238 --> 01:38:22,338
And really all it means

2887
01:38:22,338 --> 01:38:24,438
is that more of the atoms

2888
01:38:24,438 --> 01:38:26,278
are in the excited state

2889
01:38:26,278 --> 01:38:28,118
than are in the unexcited state.

2890
01:38:28,378 --> 01:38:29,558
That's all it really means.

2891
01:38:30,158 --> 01:38:32,638
Wouldn't that be a good example of

2892
01:38:33,238 --> 01:38:35,938
if you had a tool like a generalized temperature

2893
01:38:35,938 --> 01:38:38,898
that was a function of the entropy

2894
01:38:38,898 --> 01:38:42,478
as well as the energy that would...

2895
01:38:42,478 --> 01:38:43,578
In other words,

2896
01:38:43,578 --> 01:38:44,478
the temperature,

2897
01:38:45,838 --> 01:38:47,998
it's related to the energy

2898
01:38:47,998 --> 01:38:50,158
given that it's in thermal equilibrium,

2899
01:38:50,478 --> 01:38:53,558
which means the entropy is mass-alized.

2900
01:38:53,798 --> 01:38:54,138
Mm-hmm.

2901
01:38:54,158 --> 01:38:54,438
Okay.

2902
01:38:55,638 --> 01:38:57,098
In this situation,

2903
01:38:57,098 --> 01:38:58,698
when you're not at that high point,

2904
01:38:58,858 --> 01:39:03,918
the system is not in thermal equilibrium.

2905
01:39:04,478 --> 01:39:04,838
Well,

2906
01:39:04,838 --> 01:39:06,538
it's technically in thermal equilibrium

2907
01:39:06,538 --> 01:39:07,418
when it's over here.

2908
01:39:07,878 --> 01:39:09,018
Why would it be that?

2909
01:39:09,238 --> 01:39:10,718
Because the entropy is mass-alized.

2910
01:39:11,338 --> 01:39:11,878
Yeah.

2911
01:39:12,478 --> 01:39:14,838
The entropy is maximized for a given amount of energy,

2912
01:39:15,038 --> 01:39:17,318
but now the energy is greater than...

2913
01:39:18,598 --> 01:39:20,978
than the energy would be at infinite temperature.

2914
01:39:23,518 --> 01:39:24,038
Yeah.

2915
01:39:24,258 --> 01:39:25,038
I mean,

2916
01:39:25,038 --> 01:39:27,458
it's still governed by the Boltzmann distribution,

2917
01:39:27,858 --> 01:39:30,298
but a Boltzmann distribution with a negative temperature.

2918
01:39:31,298 --> 01:39:31,818
So,

2919
01:39:31,818 --> 01:39:32,558
as I said,

2920
01:39:32,558 --> 01:39:33,318
the only obstruction

2921
01:39:33,318 --> 01:39:36,638
to writing down mathematically negative temperatures

2922
01:39:37,358 --> 01:39:39,318
is that as a general rule,

2923
01:39:39,518 --> 01:39:41,338
if you put a negative temperature over here,

2924
01:39:41,338 --> 01:39:43,678
the partition function would just be infinite,

2925
01:39:43,898 --> 01:39:45,998
just because the series wouldn't converge.

2926
01:39:46,678 --> 01:39:47,278
If,

2927
01:39:47,278 --> 01:39:48,098
for some reason,

2928
01:39:48,098 --> 01:39:50,298
there's an upper bound on the energy,

2929
01:39:50,498 --> 01:39:52,818
then negative temperature makes mathematical sense,

2930
01:39:53,438 --> 01:39:57,038
but it still may not make the same physical sense

2931
01:39:57,038 --> 01:39:58,578
that it would for negative...

2932
01:39:58,578 --> 01:39:59,438
for positive temperatures.

2933
01:39:59,858 --> 01:40:00,898
It wouldn't be very cold.

2934
01:40:01,318 --> 01:40:02,998
It wouldn't be very cold.

2935
01:40:03,078 --> 01:40:04,398
It's hotter than infinity.

2936
01:40:05,038 --> 01:40:05,638
Right.

2937
01:40:06,018 --> 01:40:06,758
You know,

2938
01:40:06,758 --> 01:40:07,858
consider a...

2939
01:40:07,858 --> 01:40:10,838
consider a following situation where you have a laser gain,

2940
01:40:11,398 --> 01:40:12,698
a helium-magnet laser,

2941
01:40:12,798 --> 01:40:13,958
and you've got...

2942
01:40:13,958 --> 01:40:16,138
maybe you're exciting it optically,

2943
01:40:16,258 --> 01:40:18,088
and so you've got a

2944
01:40:18,088 --> 01:40:19,918
constant bath of photons coming in

2945
01:40:19,918 --> 01:40:21,258
and exciting the states in the...

2946
01:40:21,258 --> 01:40:21,818
in the mass.

2947
01:40:22,038 --> 01:40:22,218
Right.

2948
01:40:22,338 --> 01:40:23,958
A little bit of energy going off the side.

2949
01:40:25,238 --> 01:40:26,778
If you were to take that gas

2950
01:40:26,778 --> 01:40:28,398
and divide it into smaller volumes,

2951
01:40:29,357 --> 01:40:31,338
wouldn't all those volumes have the same statistics?

2952
01:40:31,498 --> 01:40:32,098
And in that sense,

2953
01:40:32,158 --> 01:40:33,538
wouldn't that be that it's an equilibrium?

2954
01:40:34,658 --> 01:40:35,498
Equilibrium with itself,

2955
01:40:35,598 --> 01:40:38,198
but not equilibrium with the environment of the laser.

2956
01:40:38,638 --> 01:40:39,838
Because we're putting energy in?

2957
01:40:39,958 --> 01:40:40,498
Is that the...?

2958
01:40:40,838 --> 01:40:41,018
Well,

2959
01:40:41,018 --> 01:40:41,258
yeah.

2960
01:40:41,418 --> 01:40:41,578
I mean,

2961
01:40:41,578 --> 01:40:41,778
we...

2962
01:40:41,778 --> 01:40:44,718
My only point is that you couldn't get the system

2963
01:40:44,718 --> 01:40:45,798
to be at negative temperature

2964
01:40:45,798 --> 01:40:49,378
by placing it in a bathtub of water

2965
01:40:49,378 --> 01:40:50,718
at negative temperature.

2966
01:40:51,818 --> 01:40:52,798
You wouldn't...

2967
01:40:54,458 --> 01:40:57,398
The way that you get systems at negative temperature

2968
01:40:57,398 --> 01:40:59,678
is not to let them equilibrate

2969
01:40:59,678 --> 01:41:01,298
with systems in thermal equilibrium,

2970
01:41:01,458 --> 01:41:03,818
but it's to do something very far from thermal equilibrium.

2971
01:41:06,138 --> 01:41:06,998
And then,

2972
01:41:06,998 --> 01:41:07,358
yes,

2973
01:41:07,438 --> 01:41:08,978
if you manage to get

2974
01:41:08,978 --> 01:41:10,518
the system into this population inversion,

2975
01:41:10,518 --> 01:41:11,078
configuration,

2976
01:41:12,357 --> 01:41:16,298
I presume that the molecules will exchange some energy

2977
01:41:16,298 --> 01:41:19,298
and do some things which will get it into...

2978
01:41:19,298 --> 01:41:21,138
which will get the pieces of it

2979
01:41:21,138 --> 01:41:23,998
into thermal equilibrium at the negative temperature.

2980
01:41:24,278 --> 01:41:26,118
But they won't be in thermal equilibrium

2981
01:41:26,118 --> 01:41:27,998
with an external heat bath.

2982
01:41:28,318 --> 01:41:29,318
That's all I mean.

2983
01:41:29,458 --> 01:41:29,558
Yeah.

2984
01:41:30,298 --> 01:41:31,638
They may define...

2985
01:41:32,518 --> 01:41:36,678
The extent to which they define in any sense,

2986
01:41:36,858 --> 01:41:38,098
in any useful sense,

2987
01:41:38,098 --> 01:41:41,858
a heat bath at negative temperature.

2988
01:41:42,918 --> 01:41:44,398
That's a peculiar question.

2989
01:41:44,598 --> 01:41:44,778
I mean,

2990
01:41:44,778 --> 01:41:46,718
I'm not sure if you took some...

2991
01:41:48,118 --> 01:41:48,678
Maybe.

2992
01:41:48,978 --> 01:41:49,718
I have to...

2993
01:41:49,718 --> 01:41:51,018
We'd have to invent a case

2994
01:41:51,018 --> 01:41:52,318
and see what it would mean.

2995
01:41:52,718 --> 01:41:55,598
Can we bring another laser to thermal equilibrium

2996
01:41:55,598 --> 01:41:56,658
at negative temperature

2997
01:41:56,658 --> 01:41:59,898
by putting it in contact with a laser at negative...?

2998
01:41:59,898 --> 01:42:00,498
Maybe.

2999
01:42:00,498 --> 01:42:01,178
I'm not sure.

3000
01:42:02,978 --> 01:42:04,098
Interesting question.

3001
